\pard\ql\b\fs28 RECITALS\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard\ql\fs22\b WHEREAS:\b0\par
\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22
A.\tab The Company operates a healthtech business and seeks to expand its commercial operations through improved go-to-market capabilities;\par
\par
B.\tab The Contractor is an independent professional with expertise in commercial strategy, software development, and growth operations;\par
\par
C.\tab The Contractor operates as a self-employed professional (trabalhador independente) under Portuguese law and issues invoices via the Portuguese Tax Authority's Recibos Verdes system;\par
\par
D.\tab Both parties wish to establish a clear framework for the provision of services, compensation, and mutual obligations;\par
\par
\pard\ql\fs22\b NOW, THEREFORE,\b0  the parties agree as follows:\par
\par
\pard\qc ____________________________________________________________________________________\par
\par

\pard\ql\b\fs28 ARTICLE 1: NATURE OF RELATIONSHIP\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard\ql\fs22\b 1.1 Independent Contractor Status.\b0  The Contractor is engaged as an independent contractor (prestataire de services / prestador de servi\'e7os) and not as an employee. There is no relationship of subordination (lien de subordination) between the parties.\par
\par
\b 1.2 No Employment Relationship.\b0  This Agreement does not create an employment contract (contrat de travail / contrato de trabalho). The Contractor:\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22
\'95\tab Determines their own working hours and methods\par
\'95\tab Provides their own equipment and workspace\par
\'95\tab Is responsible for their own taxes, social security, and insurance\par
\'95\tab May provide services to other clients\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par
\b 1.3 EU Services Freedom.\b0  This Agreement is entered into under the freedom to provide services within the European Union, in accordance with Articles 56-62 of the Treaty on the Functioning of the European Union (TFEU).\par
\par

\pard\ql\b\fs28 ARTICLE 2: SCOPE OF SERVICES\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard\ql\fs22\b 2.1 Primary Services.\b0  The Contractor agrees to provide the following services:\par
\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22\b A) GTM System Development\b0\par
\pard\li1080\ql\fs22
\'95\tab Custom Go-To-Market web application\par
\'95\tab AI-personalized bulk email campaign functionality\par
\'95\tab Lead import and management system\par
\'95\tab Sales pipeline visualization dashboard\par
\'95\tab Email open/click tracking and analytics\par
\'95\tab Campaign scheduling and management interface\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22\par
\b B) Commercial Growth Services\b0\par
\pard\li1080\ql\fs22
\'95\tab Outbound lead generation and prospecting\par
\'95\tab Sales campaign design and execution\par
\'95\tab Pipeline management and optimization\par
\'95\tab Performance reporting\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par
\b 2.2 Minimum Viable Product (MVP).\b0  The GTM system MVP shall include the core features listed in 2.1(A) in functional, deployable form suitable for business operations.\par
\par
\b 2.3 Time Commitment.\b0  The Contractor commits to approximately fifteen to twenty (15-20) hours per week during the term of this Agreement.\par
\par
\b 2.4 Exclusions.\b0  Unless separately agreed in writing, Services do not include: hardware procurement, third-party software licenses, legal or accounting advice, or in-person attendance at Company premises.\par
\par

