\pard\ql\fs22\par

\pard\ql\b\fs28 ARTICLE 4: INVOICING AND TAX COMPLIANCE\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard\ql\fs22\b 4.1 Invoicing.\b0  The Contractor shall issue invoices (Fatura-Recibo) via the Portuguese Tax Authority portal (Portal das Finan\'e7as) for all amounts due.\par
\par
\b 4.2 Invoice Requirements.\b0  Each invoice shall include:\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22
\'95\tab Contractor's name, address, and Portuguese NIF\par
\'95\tab Company's name, address, and SIRET/registration number\par
\'95\tab Description of services rendered\par
\'95\tab Amount in EUR\par
\'95\tab VAT notation as per Article 4.3\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par
\b 4.3 VAT Treatment.\b0  As an intra-EU B2B service:\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22
\'95\tab If Contractor is VAT-exempt (regime de isen\'e7\'e3o): Invoice states \i "IVA \'96 regime de isen\'e7\'e3o, artigo 53.\'ba do CIVA"\i0\par
\'95\tab If reverse charge applies: Invoice states \i "IVA \'96 autoliquida\'e7\'e3o / Reverse charge \'96 Article 196, EU VAT Directive 2006/112/EC"\i0\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par
\b 4.4 Tax Responsibility.\b0  The Contractor is solely responsible for:\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22
\'95\tab Portuguese income tax (IRS) obligations\par
\'95\tab Portuguese social security (Seguran\'e7a Social) contributions\par
\'95\tab Any applicable VAT obligations\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par
\b 4.5 No Withholding.\b0  The Company shall pay gross amounts without withholding, as no withholding tax applies to EU cross-border B2B services between Portugal and France.\par
\par

\pard\ql\b\fs28 ARTICLE 5: DELIVERABLES AND TIMELINE\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard\ql\fs22\b 5.1 MVP Delivery Deadline.\b0  The Contractor shall deliver a functional GTM System MVP within six (6) weeks of receiving the Advance Payment.\par
\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22
Advance Payment Received:\tab\tab _______________________ (Date)\par
MVP Deadline:\tab\tab\tab _______________________ (Date)\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par
\b 5.2 Progress Reporting.\b0  The Contractor shall provide weekly written updates including:\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22
\'95\tab Hours worked during the period\par
\'95\tab Tasks completed\par
\'95\tab Tasks planned for the following week\par
\'95\tab Blockers, risks, or concerns\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par
\b 5.3 Acceptance Process.\b0  The Company shall have seven (7) calendar days following MVP delivery to:\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22
\'95\tab Review the deliverables\par
\'95\tab Request reasonable modifications\par
\'95\tab Provide written acceptance or objections\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par
If no written response is received within seven (7) days, the MVP shall be deemed accepted.\par
\par

\pard\ql\b\fs28 ARTICLE 6: ADVANCE REFUND CONDITIONS\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard\ql\fs22\b 6.1 Refund Triggers (Contractor Responsibility).\b0  The Contractor shall refund a proportionate amount of the Advance if:\par
\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22
(a)\tab Contractor ceases communication for fourteen (14) or more consecutive days without valid reason;\par
(b)\tab Contractor explicitly terminates before MVP delivery without mutual consent;\par
(c)\tab Contractor fails to deliver MVP by deadline (excluding Company-caused delays).\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par
\b 6.2 Refund Calculation.\b0\par
\par
\pard\qc\fs22\i Refund Amount = Advance Payment \'96 (Hours Worked \'d7 Hourly Rate)\i0\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par
Hours Worked shall be determined by the weekly progress reports under Article 5.2.\par
\par
\b 6.3 No Refund Conditions.\b0  The Contractor retains the full Advance with no refund obligation if:\par
\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22
(a)\tab MVP is delivered as specified;\par
(b)\tab Company terminates for reasons other than Contractor's material breach;\par
(c)\tab Company fails to respond for fourteen (14) or more consecutive days;\par
(d)\tab Company materially changes scope without written agreement;\par
(e)\tab Mutual agreement to end after equivalent hours worked;\par
(f)\tab Force majeure, illness, or emergency (with prompt communication).\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par
\b 6.4 Refund Timeline.\b0  Any refund due shall be paid within thirty (30) calendar days of the triggering event.\par
\par

\pard\ql\b\fs28 ARTICLE 7: INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard\ql\fs22\b 7.1 Assignment.\b0  Upon full payment of all compensation due under this Agreement, all intellectual property rights in the GTM system and deliverables created under this Agreement shall transfer to the Company.\par
\par
\b 7.2 Pre-Existing IP.\b0  The Contractor retains all rights to pre-existing tools, frameworks, libraries, and methodologies. The Company receives a perpetual, non-exclusive license to use any pre-existing IP incorporated in the deliverables.\par
\par
\b 7.3 Interim License.\b0  Until full payment is received, the Company receives a limited, revocable license to use the deliverables for internal business purposes only.\par
\par

\pard\ql\b\fs28 ARTICLE 8: CONFIDENTIALITY\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard\ql\fs22\b 8.1 Confidential Information.\b0  Both parties agree to maintain the confidentiality of proprietary information disclosed during the engagement, including: business strategies, customer data, technical specifications, pricing, and financial information.\par
\par
\b 8.2 Duration.\b0  Confidentiality obligations survive termination for two (2) years.\par
\par
\b 8.3 Permitted Disclosures.\b0  Confidentiality obligations do not apply to information that:\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22
(a)\tab Becomes publicly available through no fault of the receiving party;\par
(b)\tab Was already known to the receiving party prior to disclosure;\par
(c)\tab Is independently developed by the receiving party;\par
(d)\tab Is required to be disclosed by law or court order.\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par

\pard\ql\b\fs28 ARTICLE 9: GOOD FAITH AND DISPUTE RESOLUTION\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard\ql\fs22\b 9.1 Good Faith.\b0  Both parties commit to acting in good faith and communicating openly about any concerns or issues.\par
\par
\b 9.2 Notice Before Breach Claim.\b0  Neither party may claim material breach without first providing seven (7) days written notice specifying:\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22
\'95\tab The alleged breach\par
\'95\tab The remedy requested\par
\'95\tab A reasonable opportunity to cure\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par
\b 9.3 Escalation Process.\b0\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22
Step 1: Direct Discussion\tab\tab 14 days \'96 Parties attempt to resolve directly\par
Step 2: Mediation\tab\tab\tab 30 days \'96 Neutral third-party mediation\par
Step 3: Legal Action\tab\tab\tab If mediation fails \'96 Court proceedings\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par
\b 9.4 Jurisdiction.\b0  Any legal proceedings shall be brought before the courts of:\par
\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22
\uc0\u9744  Paris, France\par
\uc0\u9744  Lisbon, Portugal\par
\uc0\u9744  Other: _________________________________\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par
\i (Tick one by mutual agreement)\i0\par
\par

\pard\ql\b\fs28 ARTICLE 10: TERM AND TERMINATION\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard\ql\fs22\b 10.1 Initial Term.\b0  This Agreement begins on the Effective Date and continues for three (3) months.\par
\par
\b 10.2 Renewal.\b0  After the initial term, this Agreement renews month-to-month unless either party provides fourteen (14) days written notice of non-renewal.\par
\par
\b 10.3 Termination for Convenience.\b0  Either party may terminate with fourteen (14) days written notice, subject to the refund provisions in Article 6.\par
\par
\b 10.4 Termination for Cause.\b0  Either party may terminate immediately upon material breach, following the notice procedure in Article 9.2.\par
\par
\b 10.5 Effect of Termination.\b0  Upon termination:\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22
\'95\tab All unpaid amounts become immediately due\par
\'95\tab Confidentiality obligations continue per Article 8.2\par
\'95\tab IP provisions apply per Article 7\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par

\pard\ql\b\fs28 ARTICLE 11: GENERAL PROVISIONS\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard\ql\fs22\b 11.1 Language.\b0  This Agreement is drafted in English by mutual consent of the parties.\par
\par
\b 11.2 Governing Law.\b0  This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with:\par
\par
\pard\li720\ql\fs22
\uc0\u9744  French law (droit fran\'e7ais)\par
\uc0\u9744  Portuguese law (lei portuguesa)\par
\uc0\u9744  Other: _________________________________\par
\pard\ql\fs22\par
\i (Tick one by mutual agreement)\i0\par
\par
\b 11.3 Entire Agreement.\b0  This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties and supersedes all prior negotiations, representations, and agreements.\par
\par
\b 11.4 Amendments.\b0  Any amendments must be in writing and signed by both parties.\par
\par
\b 11.5 Severability.\b0  If any provision is found unenforceable, the remaining provisions continue in full effect.\par
\par
\b 11.6 Notices.\b0  All notices shall be in writing and sent via email to the addresses specified in the Parties section, with read receipt requested.\par
\par
\b 11.7 Counterparts.\b0  This Agreement may be executed in counterparts, including electronic signatures, each of which shall constitute an original.\par
\par
